==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neo-Lamarckism
<hw>Ne`o-La*marck"ism</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Lamarckism as revived, modified, and expounded by recent
biologists, esp. as maintaining that the offspring inherits characters
acquired by the parent from change of environment, use or disuse of
parts, etc.; -- opposed of <contr>Neo-Darwinism</contr> (which see,
above).</def> <note>This theory has been thoroughly discredited, though
it had some support for a time in the Soviet Union due to the influence
of the biologist <persfn>Lysenko</persfn>.</note>--
<wordforms><wf>Ne`o-La*marck"i*an</wf>, <pos>a.</pos> &
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neo-Latin</ent>⟦br⟧
